headline.main: STEP ANGERS ROME; Fleet Move Increases Italian Resentment Toward Allies PEACE ASSURANCE LIMITED Ciano Tells U.S. Envoy It Goes for Only Ten Days--Denies Designs on Yugoslavia

lead_paragraph: ROME, May 2--United States Ambassador William Phillips's colloquy with Premier Mussolini yesterday was followed today by another meeting with Count Ciano, the Italian Foreign Minister. The Ambassador remained at the Palazzo Chigi more than half an hour. It was the third time this week that Mr. Phillips had talked with Count Ciano.
